From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000007 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Jun 2026 09:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] clk: ti: composite: implement divider round_rate/set_rate

OMAP4 "ti,composite-clock" nodes (gate + divider, no mux) wire their rate
component to ti_composite_divider_ops. While .recalc_rate delegates to the
real ti_clk_divider_ops, .round_rate and .set_rate were left as stubs that
unconditionally return -EINVAL. The generic clk-composite core therefore
exposes only a round_rate that always fails, so any clk_set_rate() on such a
clock (e.g. via assigned-clock-rates) returns -EINVAL.

On the Google Nexus Q (steelhead) this breaks the TAS5713 amplifier MCLK
path: the DTS sets dpll_per_m3x2_ck to 61.44 MHz (-> auxclk1 /5 ->
fref_clk1_out 12.288 MHz = 256 x 48 kHz), but the assignment fails with:

  clk: couldn't set dpll_per_m3x2_ck clk rate to 61440000 (-22),
       current rate: 256000000

leaving auxclk1 at 16 MHz and the amplifier without a correct master clock.

Delegate round_rate and set_rate to ti_clk_divider_ops, exactly as
recalc_rate already does. The rate_hw passed to these ops is the divider's
clk_hw (recalc_rate already operates on it successfully), so the divider ops
apply unchanged. This lets a composite divider's rate be rounded and set,
matching what the vendor board-steelhead.c clock setup did.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petr.parkan.janda@oh-so.com>
---
 drivers/clk/ti/composite.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/clk/ti/composite.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/ti/composite.c
@@ -29,13 +29,13 @@
 static long ti_composite_round_rate(struct clk_hw *hw, unsigned long rate,
 				    unsigned long *prate)
 {
-	return -EINVAL;
+	return ti_clk_divider_ops.round_rate(hw, rate, prate);
 }
 
 static int ti_composite_set_rate(struct clk_hw *hw, unsigned long rate,
 				 unsigned long parent_rate)
 {
-	return -EINVAL;
+	return ti_clk_divider_ops.set_rate(hw, rate, parent_rate);
 }
 
 static const struct clk_ops ti_composite_divider_ops = {
